<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-08-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="209" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d209">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Wood</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 6.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/><placeName><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-08-01"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 1, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 11th of July last has
                            been received, and the President instructs me to say that the
                            explanation of the views of the Danish government given to you by Mr.
                            Hall, the minister for foreign affairs, is very satisfactory.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer><signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Bradford R. Wood</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c., Copenhagen</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>